steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"5uc41","text":"If infecting transfected cells, infect them 24 hours after transfection. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9saki","text":"Replace media with fresh media (with FBS) prior to infection with GFP-VSV.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cq36v","text":"Dilute VSV-GFP in serum-free culture media. Perform the necessary calculations to determine the dilution that is required to obtain the desired MOI (multiplicity of infection).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1lh6","text":"Note: MOI is the number of viruses/number of cells. For example, a MOI of 1 = 500,000 PFU (plaque forming units) of virus per 500,000 cells. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":0,"length":4}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c3gl6","text":"Note: We typically start with a dilution range of MOI = 0.01, 0.1, 1 for optimization","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":0,"length":4}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9k66d","text":"Infect cells by dropping the diluted virus directly into the wells making sure to disperse the virus around the well. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fajqs","text":"Gently swirl the plate to help disperse the virus. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6c8sk","text":"Leave the plate for approximately 24 hours in a 37°C CO2 incubator. Then proceed with endpoint analysis.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":55,"length":2}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
